user_prompt_template:
CHAPTER NARRATIVE (read this carefully — every rule, trigger, scenario, and metric must come directly from this content):
{chapter_narrative}

CHAPTER PLAN:
{current_chapter_json}

PROJECT CONTEXT:
Life Event: {life_event}
Document: {document_title}
Audience: {audience}
Tone: {tone}
Context: {context}

Generate the structural elements for {domain_name}. Every element must be directly grounded in the narrative provided above.

QUICK REFERENCE RULES (5–8 rules):
  • Surface the most critical operational decisions from the narrative
  • Each rule: immediately actionable by a non-expert on day one
  • Format: "Rule text — Rationale: why this rule exists. Trigger: the specific condition that activates it. Risk: the concrete consequence of ignoring it."

SCENARIO SCENE (required — 3–5 sentences):
  A real-world mini-story showing this chapter's system working as designed.
  Named character + specific time pressure + at least one number or dollar figure + positive outcome that required the system.
  Written in present tense.

SUCCESS METRICS (3–5 metrics):
  Specific, quantified outcomes the operator achieves when this chapter's system works.
  Each metric must include at least one concrete value: hours saved, dollars protected, days avoided, number of actions completed, specific risk neutralised.

CASCADE TRIGGERS:
  Name the conditions in this chapter that activate required actions in other domains.
  Format: "When [specific condition in this chapter], immediately trigger [specific action in other domain/chapter]."

Return ONLY the following JSON object. No prose. No markdown. No code fences.

{{
  "chapter_number": {chapter_number},
  "domain_id": "domain ID from the chapter plan",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter title from the plan",
  "quick_reference_rules": [
    "Rule text — Rationale: why this rule exists. Trigger: the specific condition that activates it. Risk: the concrete consequence of ignoring it."
  ],
  "cascade_triggers": [
    "When [specific condition in this chapter], immediately trigger [specific action in other domain/chapter]"
  ],
  "scenario_scene": "3–5 sentence present-tense mini-story. Named character, specific time pressure, at least one number or dollar figure, positive outcome that required the system.",
  "success_metrics": [
    "Specific quantified outcome — must include at least one concrete value (hours, dollars, days, count, or risk)"
  ]
}}
